## Step 3: Create Database Template Record

Insert a new Information Request Template into the database.

### SQL: Insert Template Record

```sql
-- Insert into INFORMATION_REQUEST_TEMPLATE table
INSERT INTO INFORMATION_REQUEST_TEMPLATE (
    ID,
    TITLE,
    TYPE,
    STATE,
    SEND_TO_APPLICANT,
    SEND_TO_RECRUITER,
    IS_HARDCOPY,
    CREATION_DATE,
    CREATED_BY
) VALUES (
    INFORMATION_REQUEST_TEMPLATE_SEQ.NEXTVAL,  -- Auto-generated ID
    'Employment Verification - SIDB',           -- Template title
    'EMAIL',                                     -- EMAIL or HARDCOPY
    'ACTIVE',                                    -- ACTIVE or INACTIVE
    'Y',                                         -- Send to applicant
    'Y',                                         -- Send to recruiter
    'N',                                         -- Is hardcopy
    SYSDATE,                                     -- Creation timestamp
    'ADMIN'                                      -- Created by operator
);

-- Get the generated ID for next steps
SELECT INFORMATION_REQUEST_TEMPLATE_SEQ.CURRVAL AS TEMPLATE_ID FROM DUAL;
```

